alwaysApply: true


This file defines the Cursor (CLI / code generator / editor assistant) role for the Tutor GPT project. The Cursor role is intended to be given to a code-generation agent (or the Cursor IDE assistant) that will read the project docs (Flow + Technical + prompts) and generate production-ready code, tests, CI, Docker, and deployment artifacts. The Cursor role must follow the Project Constitution exactly.

High-level responsibilities

Read the project docs and prompts (agents_prompts/*.md). Do not assume unstated behavior.

Generate code backend-first (FastAPI + Agents SDK using Gemini), then frontend (Next.js). Follow the task list in the Technical doc.

Create modular, testable code, with one coherent unit per commit. Add meaningful commit messages and ADRs when making architecture changes.

Always use MCPs (Context7, TAVILY, Playwright) as configured — do not produce static, hardcoded search or web-scraping code. Use provided MCP tools and cache/limit usage.

Use dynamic prompt files (agents_prompts/*.md). Do not bake prompts into code; load prompts at startup.

Wire tools (rag_tool, tavily_tool, db_tool) as typed functions and register them to Agents SDK as tools.

Register Agents SDK guardrails for input and output validation; log guardrail events to admin logs.

Operational rules (Cursor must enforce)

Backend-first: Always scaffold and test backend components before starting frontend tasks. Backend must pass CI before frontend scaffolding begins.

No static prompts: All agent prompts must live in agents_prompts/ and be editable. Cursor must create prompt templates and sample Six-Part prompts for each agent. Do not generate prompts inline in the code.

MCP-first policy: When external knowledge/search is required in generated code, wire the tutor agent to call tavily_tool (MCP) rather than embedding search code in the agent. Provide fallback behavior when MCP calls fail. Use Context7 for docs retrieval and Playwright for UI tests where needed.

Dynamic configuration: Expose model, provider, and tool settings via env vars and core/config.py. Cursor must not commit secrets; use .env.example and documentation to instruct secret usage on Render.

Type safety & validation: Generated Python code must include Pydantic models for AgentRequest/AgentResponse and input/output schemas. Include validation and schema-based guardrail checks.

Tests-first: Add unit tests for every agent and tool using mocks for Gemini, Pinecone, and TAVILY. Add integration tests for the GREETING→ASSESSMENT→PLANNING→LEARNING→QUIZ path.

CI/Pre-commit: Add GitHub Actions for tests and linters; add pre-commit hooks: black, isort, flake8, and prettier + eslint for frontend.

Logging & privacy: Log structured JSON (no secrets). Do not store raw user PII in logs. Add agent_logs table for guardrail events.

Cursor execution plan (what Cursor must generate)

init-project scaffold (folders, Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, .env.example)

startup (core/startup.py): load prompts, init DB, Redis, Pinecone, Tavily client, Gemini provider, and create Agent instances

tools/*: rag_tool, tavily_tool, db_tool (typed with retries, caching, and rate-limits)

agents/*: orchestrator_agent.py, assessment_agent.py (VARK), tutor_agent.py, quiz_agent.py, planning_agent.py, feedback_agent.py — each registered with guardrails

api/v1/*: auth.py, sessions.py, websocket.py (two-stage runner implemented), rag_router.py

frontend-skeleton: Next.js app connecting to WS and REST

tests/*: unit + integration + guardrail tests

ci/*: GitHub Actions YAML

docs/*: prompt templates (Six-Part), README, ARCHITECTURE.md, ADRs

Cursor safety & decision policy

If the prompt lacks clarity, Cursor must make a reasonable choice and document it in an ADR rather than asking the user for many clarifications.

If external credentials are required (Pinecone, Gemini, TAVILY), Cursor must generate placeholders and a README instructing the user how to set them in Render Secrets.

When generating code that calls MCPs or external tools, include retry/backoff and rate limiting wrappers.

Example commit message conventions for Cursor

feat(agents): add assessment_agent with VARK logic and tests

chore(ci): add GitHub Actions for unit tests and linters

fix(startup): handle tavily client init failure gracefully

docs(prompts): add tutor_prompt.md (Six-Part)
